data.name: lGoogleAPIInstructions.Text
data.value:
To change the Client ID and secret, first disconnect your account by clicking "Disconnect Account" above.
Obtain new values from the Google Developer Console. You'll need to enable the Calendar API in your project:

data.name: label21.Text
data.value:
On the "Google" tab, select the calendar you wish to synchronise.
If this is the first time using this application, you will need to authorise it to access your Google account. This is more secure than providing the application your username and password directly, and the process will happen automatically when you click "Retrieve Calendars".

data.name: label23.Text
data.value: The "Synchronisation Options" tab is the heart of the application. Here you specify HOW - The direction of synchronisation, and how it deals with existing entries (merging and deleting) WHEN - The date range to synchronise and whether automatically at a regular interval, push changes as they occur in Outlook, or simply manually on-demand WHAT - Choose the meeting attributes to sync: attendees, description and reminders.

data.name: label25.Text
data.value:
Finally, on the "Application Behaviour" tab, choose whether it starts automatically on login to Windows, minimises to the application tray or shows a notification bubble on sync. For helping to troubleshoot a problem, CSVs of your meetings being synchronised can be generated, and the application logging level can be altered.
If you need to access Google through a proxy, you can also provide the details here, or just rely on using Internet Explorers configuration (which is the default).
